An applicant for a license as a manufacturer or distributor shall apply for license on forms provided by the department and shall submit as part of the application process the following:
The full name, address, date of birth, and Social Security number of the applicant;
If the applicant is a corporation or other business entity, the names, addresses, dates of birth, and Social Security numbers of all officers and management personnel;
The name, address, date of birth, and Social Security number of any individual who has ten percent (10%) or more financial interest in the applicant organization;
Federal employer tax number;
A sworn statement by the applicant or the appropriate officer that all information provided is true and correct and that the applicant agrees to comply with the applicable provisions of this chapter and all applicable administrative regulations promulgated thereunder;
The name, address, and telephone number of a registered agent within the Commonwealth of Kentucky, if the applicant is not a resident; and
Any other information the department deems appropriate.

No officer, owner, employee, or contractee of a licensed distributor or licensed manufacturer or their affiliates and no member of the immediate family of an owner, officer, employee, or contractee of a licensed distributor or licensed manufacturer or their affiliates, shall, with respect to a licensed charitable organization:
Manage or otherwise be involved in the conduct of charitable gaming;
Provide bookkeeping or other accounting services related to the conduct of charitable gaming;
Handle any moneys generated in the conduct of charitable gaming;
Advise a licensed charitable organization on the expenditure of net receipts;
Provide transportation services in any manner to patrons of a charitable gaming activity;
Provide advertisement or marketing services in any manner to a licensed charitable organization;
Provide, coordinate, or solicit the services of personnel or volunteers in any manner;
Provide training or consulting on the conduct of charitable gaming, except in connection with the use of its own equipment or supplies;
Store its charitable gaming equipment or supplies in or on the premises of a licensed charitable gaming facility; or
Donate or give any prize to be awarded in the conduct of charitable gaming.
